overview: Arsenal's season literally went right down to the very last kick of the campaign - with skipper Patrick Vieira's spot kick winning the FA Cup in Cardiff. It brought a successful conclusion to another dramatic, record breaking season for the Gunners. Apart from the club's 27th major honour, there were a host of highlights in 2004/05, including an all-time league record for 49 consecutive matches without a defeat.
title: Arsenal: Season Review 2004-2005
